title: Issue 167 repeater inputs
body:
Known issue:

Bindings *on* the element (that are not a descendent) are not matched by binding(). This is possible, but requires a bunch of jQuery work that would probably be a little slow. How important is that feature?

title: Date filter should support ISO 8601 input
body:
date filter now supports input like 2009-12-31T23:00:00Z

I just wonder if we need to support input with milliseconds in the string too.

There is also a bunch of other fixes and improvements in this branch, please do not squash.

Closes #125

title: process ISO 8601 formatted date/time strings with date filter
body:
This actually just uses the parsing that the Date builtin provides.  If it fails to parse the date, behavior does not change.

Tested in FF 3.6 and Chrome 7.0.
